{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780728425369,"sessionID":"ses_164517a7effe3vNYDW5PuSLbjT","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_frCl58lGdYht75Htca8zwKQ1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/tests/conftest.py","offset":260,"limit":120},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/tests/conftest.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n260: def agent_id():\n261:     return AGENT_ID\n262: \n263: \n264: # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n265: # HTTP API client (E2E tests)\n266: # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n267: \n268: \n269: @pytest.fixture(scope=\"session\")\n270: async def _setup_app_db():\n271:     \"\"\"Ensure the APP's database (used by FastAPI routes) has schema + seed data.\"\"\"\n272:     from core_api.db.session import engine as app_engine\n273:     from common.models.base import Base\n274: \n275:     _import_all_models()\n276: \n277:     async with app_engine.begin() as conn:\n278:         await conn.execute(text(\"CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS vector\"))\n279:         await conn.run_sync(Base.metadata.create_all)\n280: \n281:     # Initialise standalone mode so the default tenant exists\n282:     from core_api.standalone import init_standalone\n283: \n284:     init_standalone()\n285: \n286:     # Wire audit hooks\n287:     from core_api.services.audit_service import log_action\n288:     from core_api.services.hooks import ServiceHooks, configure_hooks\n289: \n290:     configure_hooks(ServiceHooks(audit_log=log_action))\n291: \n292: \n293: @pytest.fixture\n294: async def client(_setup_app_db):\n295:     \"\"\"Async HTTP client for testing FastAPI endpoints.\"\"\"\n296:     from httpx import AsyncClient, ASGITransport\n297:     from core_api.app import app\n298: \n299:     transport = ASGITransport(app=app)\n300:     async with AsyncClient(transport=transport, base_url=\"http://test\") as c:\n301:         yield c\n302: \n303: \n304: # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n305: # Helpers\n306: # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n307: \n308: \n309: def make_dt(days_ago: float = 0, hours_ago: float = 0) -> datetime:\n310:     \"\"\"Create a timezone-aware datetime relative to now.\"\"\"\n311:     return datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=days_ago, hours=hours_ago)\n312: \n313: \n314: # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n315: # Platform hooks (standalone mode wiring for integration tests)\n316: # ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n317: \n318: \n319: # Re-export MCP-handler unit-test helpers so the `mcp_env` fixture is\n320: # discoverable from any test file in this directory.\n321: from tests._mcp_test_helpers import mcp_env, parse_envelope, strip_latency  # noqa: E402,F401\n322: \n323: \n324: @pytest.fixture(autouse=True)\n325: def _reset_hooks():\n326:     \"\"\"Ensure hooks are wired for integration tests.\n327: \n328:     In production, hooks are configured at app startup (lifespan).  Tests that\n329:     use the ``db`` fixture bypass the app lifespan, so we wire hooks here to\n330:     guarantee audit logging behaves identically to the running server.\n331:     \"\"\"\n332:     from core_api.services.audit_service import log_action\n333:     from core_api.services.hooks import ServiceHooks, configure_hooks, reset_hooks\n334: \n335:     configure_hooks(ServiceHooks(audit_log=log_action))\n336:     yield\n337:     reset_hooks()\n338: \n339: \n340: @pytest.fixture(scope=\"session\", autouse=True)\n341: def _disable_rate_limiter():\n342:     \"\"\"Disable the slowapi rate limiter for the whole test suite.\n343: \n344:     Tests share the admin API key and write many memories in tight\n345:     bursts (fixture setup, batched assertions) that would otherwise blow\n346:     the production write limit (10/s). Tests that specifically exercise\n347:     the rate limiter (tests/test_rate_limit.py) re-enable it locally.\n348:     \"\"\"\n349:     from core_api.middleware.rate_limit import limiter\n350: \n351:     prev = limiter.enabled\n352:     limiter.enabled = False\n353:     yield\n354:     limiter.enabled = prev\n\n(End of file - total 354 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"def agent_id():\n    return AGENT_ID\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# HTTP API client (E2E tests)\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n@pytest.fixture(scope=\"session\")\nasync def _setup_app_db():\n    \"\"\"Ensure the APP's database (used by FastAPI routes) has schema + seed data.\"\"\"\n    from core_api.db.session import engine as app_engine\n    from common.models.base import Base\n\n    _import_all_models()\n\n    async with app_engine.begin() as conn:\n        await conn.execute(text(\"CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS vector\"))\n        await conn.run_sync(Base.metadata.create_all)","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/tests/conftest.py","text":"def agent_id():\n    return AGENT_ID\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# HTTP API client (E2E tests)\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n@pytest.fixture(scope=\"session\")\nasync def _setup_app_db():\n    \"\"\"Ensure the APP's database (used by FastAPI routes) has schema + seed data.\"\"\"\n    from core_api.db.session import engine as app_engine\n    from common.models.base import Base\n\n    _import_all_models()\n\n    async with app_engine.begin() as conn:\n        await conn.execute(text(\"CREATE EXTENSION IF NOT EXISTS vector\"))\n        await conn.run_sync(Base.metadata.create_all)\n\n    # Initialise standalone mode so the default tenant exists\n    from core_api.standalone import init_standalone\n\n    init_standalone()\n\n    # Wire audit hooks\n    from core_api.services.audit_service import log_action\n    from core_api.services.hooks import ServiceHooks, configure_hooks\n\n    configure_hooks(ServiceHooks(audit_log=log_action))\n\n\n@pytest.fixture\nasync def client(_setup_app_db):\n    \"\"\"Async HTTP client for testing FastAPI endpoints.\"\"\"\n    from httpx import AsyncClient, ASGITransport\n    from core_api.app import app\n\n    transport = ASGITransport(app=app)\n    async with AsyncClient(transport=transport, base_url=\"http://test\") as c:\n        yield c\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Helpers\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\ndef make_dt(days_ago: float = 0, hours_ago: float = 0) -> datetime:\n    \"\"\"Create a timezone-aware datetime relative to now.\"\"\"\n    return datetime.now(timezone.utc) - timedelta(days=days_ago, hours=hours_ago)\n\n\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n# Platform hooks (standalone mode wiring for integration tests)\n# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------\n\n\n# Re-export MCP-handler unit-test helpers so the `mcp_env` fixture is\n# discoverable from any test file in this directory.\nfrom tests._mcp_test_helpers import mcp_env, parse_envelope, strip_latency  # noqa: E402,F401\n\n\n@pytest.fixture(autouse=True)\ndef _reset_hooks():\n    \"\"\"Ensure hooks are wired for integration tests.\n\n    In production, hooks are configured at app startup (lifespan).  Tests that\n    use the ``db`` fixture bypass the app lifespan, so we wire hooks here to\n    guarantee audit logging behaves identically to the running server.\n    \"\"\"\n    from core_api.services.audit_service import log_action\n    from core_api.services.hooks import ServiceHooks, configure_hooks, reset_hooks\n\n    configure_hooks(ServiceHooks(audit_log=log_action))\n    yield\n    reset_hooks()\n\n\n@pytest.fixture(scope=\"session\", autouse=True)\ndef _disable_rate_limiter():\n    \"\"\"Disable the slowapi rate limiter for the whole test suite.\n\n    Tests share the admin API key and write many memories in tight\n    bursts (fixture setup, batched assertions) that would otherwise blow\n    the production write limit (10/s). Tests that specifically exercise\n    the rate limiter (tests/test_rate_limit.py) re-enable it locally.\n    \"\"\"\n    from core_api.middleware.rate_limit import limiter\n\n    prev = limiter.enabled\n    limiter.enabled = False\n    yield\n    limiter.enabled = prev","lineStart":260,"lineEnd":354,"totalLines":354,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/tests/conftest.py","time":{"start":1780728425359,"end":1780728425368}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0336b23a44de4dc5016a23c26940008191b4011052921b606f"}},"id":"prt_e9baf6b8e001vidMboa5EY93PE","sessionID":"ses_164517a7effe3vNYDW5PuSLbjT","messageID":"msg_e9baf44e00018JKlzY23UWrTRW"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780728425375,"sessionID":"ses_164517a7effe3vNYDW5PuSLbjT","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_5ID0ucYbuVYAE4Qww1sjJy42","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"^## Performance|LoCoMo|LongMemEval|Token savings|Accuracy|Search latency|What we measure|benchmarks","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/README.md","include":"README.md"},"output":"Found 11 matches\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/README.md:\n  Line 36: **Built for fleets, not single agents.** Public agent-memory benchmarks (LoCoMo, LongMemEval) measure one agent, one user, one long conversation — the single-chatbot shape. The deployment shape we see in production is the opposite: dozens or thousands of agents working on behalf of a company, sharing what they learn under governance. MemClaw is architected around that shape from day one — scoped memory, cross-agent outcome propagation, fleet-wide trust tiers — and competes on the axes that compound with agent count: latency, token efficiency, and governance. See [Performance](#performance) for the numbers, or read the [benchmarks write-up](https://memclaw.net/blog/memclaw-benchmarks).\n\n  Line 279: ## Performance\n\n  Line 281: Benchmarked against the two most-cited public agent-memory benchmarks. Methodology and operator-scale context live in [`docs/performance.md`](docs/performance.md); the full write-up is on the blog.\n\n  Line 283: |  | LoCoMo | LongMemEval | Search latency |\n\n  Line 285: | Accuracy (LLM-judge) | **77.6%** | **72.5%** | — |\n\n  Line 286: | Token savings vs full context | **96.6%** | **98.2%** | — |\n\n  Line 289: Accuracy sits inside the leading cluster across the field (Mem0, Zep, MemClaw — scores cluster in a narrow band). The axes we push hardest are latency and token efficiency, because those are the ones that compound as agent count grows — a few hundred ms of search latency disappears behind one LLM call, but bills millions of times a day across a fleet.\n\n  Line 291: > Single-agent benchmarks can't measure cross-agent recall, outcome propagation between agents, fleet-scoped visibility, or governance-aware retrieval. Those are the questions that decide whether a memory system is *deployable* inside a company. See [`docs/performance.md`](docs/performance.md#what-these-benchmarks-cant-measure).\n\n  Line 293: Source: [Fast, Token-Efficient, and Built for Fleets](https://memclaw.net/blog/memclaw-benchmarks) (2026-04-19).\n\n  Line 783: ├── scripts/                       # Smoke tests, benchmarks, export tools\n\n  Line 792: <summary>Latency benchmarks</summary>\n","metadata":{"matches":11,"truncated":false},"title":"^## Performance|LoCoMo|LongMemEval|Token savings|Accuracy|Search latency|What we measure|benchmarks","time":{"start":1780728425347,"end":1780728425371}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0336b23a44de4dc5016a23c2693fe881918dbc9a78738016a3"}},"id":"prt_e9baf6b5e00186M3OWXH7qd53Z","sessionID":"ses_164517a7effe3vNYDW5PuSLbjT","messageID":"msg_e9baf44e00018JKlzY23UWrTRW"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780728425375,"sessionID":"ses_164517a7effe3vNYDW5PuSLbjT","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_WP9UIKwyzHKdIjpXfIEAowT6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/README.md","offset":760,"limit":130},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n760: │       ├── auth.py                # API key + JWT auth, tenant enforcement\n761: │       ├── routes/                # Route handlers\n762: │       ├── services/              # Business logic\n763: │       ├── providers/             # LLM/embedding abstraction + fallback\n764: │       ├── pipeline/              # Composable write/search pipelines\n765: │       └── tools/                 # MCP tool implementations\n766: │\n767: ├── core-storage-api/              # PostgreSQL CRUD microservice\n768: │   └── src/core_storage_api/\n769: │       ├── routers/               # Memory, entity, document, fleet CRUD\n770: │       ├── services/              # ORM operations\n771: │       └── database/              # SQLAlchemy models, Alembic migrations\n772: │\n773: ├── plugin/                        # OpenClaw plugin (TypeScript)\n774: │   └── src/\n775: │       ├── tools.ts               # Tool implementations\n776: │       ├── agent-auth.ts          # Per-agent credentials (agent-scoped mc_ keys)\n777: │       ├── context-engine.ts      # Auto-read/write lifecycle\n778: │       ├── heartbeat.ts           # 60s heartbeat → MemClaw API\n779: │       └── educate.ts             # Agent education delivery\n780: │\n781: ├── common/                        # Shared SQLAlchemy ORM models and constants\n782: ├── tests/                         # Test suite\n783: ├── scripts/                       # Smoke tests, benchmarks, export tools\n784: ├── docker-compose.yml             # Production-like stack\n785: ├── docker-compose.dev.yml         # Dev stack\n786: └── .env.example                   # Full configuration reference\n787: ```\n788: \n789: </details>\n790: \n791: <details>\n792: <summary>Latency benchmarks</summary>\n793: \n794: Typical results on a single-instance deployment (OpenAI embeddings + GPT-5.4 Nano):\n795: \n796: | Operation | Mean | P50 | P95 |\n797: |---|---|---|---|\n798: | `memclaw_write` | ~2000ms | ~2000ms | ~2300ms |\n799: | `memclaw_recall` | ~650ms | ~640ms | ~670ms |\n800: | `memclaw_recall` (with `include_brief=true`) | ~1300ms | ~1200ms | ~2100ms |\n801: \n802: Write latency is dominated by LLM enrichment. Recall latency by the embedding API call.\n803: \n804: ```bash\n805: python scripts/latency_test.py --url http://localhost:8000 --api-key <admin-key> --runs 20\n806: ```\n807: \n808: </details>\n809: \n810: ---\n811: \n812: ## Public API & Stability\n813: \n814: MemClaw v1.x follows [SemVer 2.0.0](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html). The surfaces below are stable; everything else is internal and may change in any release.\n815: \n816: ### Stable surfaces\n817: \n818: #### MCP tools (12)\n819: \n820: The MCP server is mounted at `/mcp`. Tool names, parameter names, and the documented op-dispatch values are stable.\n821: \n822: | Tool | Purpose |\n823: |---|---|\n824: | `memclaw_recall` | Hybrid semantic + keyword search over memories, with optional LLM-summarised brief. |\n825: | `memclaw_write` | Single or batch (≤100) memory write; auto-enriched with type, title, summary, tags. |\n826: | `memclaw_manage` | Per-memory lifecycle, op-dispatched: `read` \\| `update` \\| `transition` \\| `delete` \\| `bulk_delete` \\| `lineage`. |\n827: | `memclaw_list` | Non-semantic enumeration with filters, sort, cursor pagination. |\n828: | `memclaw_doc` | Structured-document CRUD, op-dispatched: `write` \\| `read` \\| `query` \\| `delete` \\| `list_collections` \\| `search`. |\n829: | `memclaw_entity_get` | Look up a knowledge-graph entity by UUID. |\n830: | `memclaw_tune` | Read/update an agent's per-search profile (top_k, fts_weight, freshness, blend, …). |\n831: | `memclaw_insights` | Karpathy-Loop reflection: contradictions, failures, stale, divergence, patterns, discover. |\n832: | `memclaw_evolve` | Karpathy-Loop feedback: record an outcome (`success` \\| `failure` \\| `partial`) against memories. |\n833: | `memclaw_stats` | Aggregate counts: total + breakdowns by `type` / `agent` / `status`. Read-only. |\n834: | `memclaw_keystones` | Read mandatory governance rules for the current scope (tenant + fleet + agent merged). Call once per session. |\n835: | `memclaw_keystones_set` | Author/remove keystone rules, op-dispatched: `set` \\| `delete`. Trust ≥ 1 for self-authored `scope=agent`; ≥ 2 otherwise. |\n836: \n837: > Skill sharing uses the generic `memclaw_doc` surface — write/read/query/search/delete on `collection=\"skills\"`. The server validates the slug and embeds `data[\"summary\"]` for semantic discovery (with a back-compat fallback to `data[\"description\"]` for skills).\n838: \n839: #### REST endpoints\n840: \n841: All paths are prefixed with `/api/v1` unless noted. Request and response shapes documented in the OpenAPI schema at `/openapi.json` are part of the contract.\n842: \n843: | Area | Endpoints |\n844: |---|---|\n845: | Memory | `GET/POST /memories`, `PATCH /memories/{id}`, `DELETE /memories/{id}`, `PATCH /memories/{id}/status`, `POST /memories/bulk`, `POST /memories/bulk-delete`, `GET /memories/stats`, `GET /memories/{id}`, `GET /memories/{id}/contradictions`, `POST /search`, `POST /recall`, `POST /ingest/preview`, `POST /ingest/commit` |\n846: | Knowledge graph | `GET /entities`, `GET /entities/{id}`, `POST /entities/upsert`, `GET /graph`, `POST /relations/upsert` |\n847: | Documents | `POST /documents`, `GET /documents`, `GET /documents/{id}`, `POST /documents/query`, `DELETE /documents/{id}` |\n848: | Keystones | `GET /memclaw/keystones`, `POST /memclaw/keystones`, `DELETE /memclaw/keystones/{doc_id}` |\n849: | Fleet | `POST /fleet/heartbeat`, `GET /fleet/nodes`, `POST /fleet/commands`, `GET /fleet/commands` |\n850: | Agents | `GET /agents`, `GET /agents/{id}`, `PATCH /agents/{id}/trust`, `POST /admin/agent-keys/provision` (atomic key + row + trust + fleet), `GET /whoami` (identity probe) |\n851: | Insights | `POST /insights/generate` |\n852: | Evolve | `POST /evolve/report` |\n853: | Crystallizer | `POST /crystallize`, `POST /crystallize/all`, `GET /crystallize/reports`, `GET /crystallize/latest` |\n854: | Settings | `GET/PUT /settings` |\n855: | System | `GET /health`, `GET /version`, `GET /tool-descriptions`, `GET /audit-log` |\n856: | MCP | `POST /mcp` (Streamable HTTP transport, mounted at app root) |\n857: | Bootstrap (plugin) | `GET /plugin-source`, `GET /plugin-source-hash`, `GET/POST /install-plugin`, `GET /install-skill`, `GET /skill/memclaw`. Aliased under `/api` (no `/v1`) for one-line installers. |\n858: \n859: #### Plugin environment variables\n860: \n861: Read by the OpenClaw plugin. The plugin's published name (`memclaw`) and these variables are the public contract; the plugin's TypeScript module structure is internal.\n862: \n863: | Var | Purpose |\n864: |---|---|\n865: | `MEMCLAW_API_URL` | Base URL of the core-api server. |\n866: | `MEMCLAW_API_KEY` | Tenant or admin API key sent in `X-API-Key`. |\n867: | `MEMCLAW_TENANT_ID` | Optional pre-resolved tenant id; bypasses lookup. |\n868: | `MEMCLAW_FLEET_ID` | Default fleet id for writes/heartbeat. |\n869: | `MEMCLAW_NODE_NAME` | Fleet node identifier reported on heartbeat. |\n870: | `MEMCLAW_AUTO_WRITE_TURNS` | Auto-write turn summaries (default `true`). |\n871: \n872: #### Server environment variables\n873: \n874: These mirror the Configuration table above. See it for defaults.\n875: \n876: | Group | Vars |\n877: |---|---|\n878: | Database | `POSTGRES_HOST`, `POSTGRES_PORT`, `POSTGRES_USER`, `POSTGRES_PASSWORD`, `POSTGRES_DB`, `POSTGRES_USE_IAM_AUTH`, `POSTGRES_REQUIRE_SSL` |\n879: | Auth | `ADMIN_API_KEY`, `MEMCLAW_API_KEY`, `IS_STANDALONE` |\n880: | Providers | `EMBEDDING_PROVIDER`, `ENTITY_EXTRACTION_PROVIDER`, `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `OPENROUTER_API_KEY`, `GEMINI_API_KEY`, `USE_LLM_FOR_MEMORY_CREATION` |\n881: | Runtime | `CORS_ORIGINS`, `ENVIRONMENT`, `SETTINGS_ENCRYPTION_KEY`, `REDIS_URL` |\n882: \n883: #### Auth modes\n884: \n885: | Mode | Activated by | Use case |\n886: |---|---|---|\n887: | Standalone | `IS_STANDALONE=true` | Single-tenant self-host; auth bypassed. |\n888: | Multi-tenant admin | `ADMIN_API_KEY=…` | Operator key for multi-tenant deployments. |\n889: | Shared gate | `MEMCLAW_API_KEY=…` | Optional shared secret required on every non-admin request. |\n\n(Showing lines 760-889 of 965. Use offset=890 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"│       ├── auth.py                # API key + JWT auth, tenant enforcement\n│       ├── routes/                # Route handlers\n│       ├── services/              # Business logic\n│       ├── providers/             # LLM/embedding abstraction + fallback\n│       ├── pipeline/              # Composable write/search pipelines\n│       └── tools/                 # MCP tool implementations\n│\n├── core-storage-api/              # PostgreSQL CRUD microservice\n│   └── src/core_storage_api/\n│       ├── routers/               # Memory, entity, document, fleet CRUD\n│       ├── services/              # ORM operations\n│       └── database/              # SQLAlchemy models, Alembic migrations\n│\n├── plugin/                        # OpenClaw plugin (TypeScript)\n│   └── src/\n│       ├── tools.ts               # Tool implementations\n│       ├── agent-auth.ts          # Per-agent credentials (agent-scoped mc_ keys)\n│       ├── context-engine.ts      # Auto-read/write lifecycle\n│       ├── heartbeat.ts           # 60s heartbeat → MemClaw API\n│       └── educate.ts             # Agent education delivery","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/README.md","text":"│       ├── auth.py                # API key + JWT auth, tenant enforcement\n│       ├── routes/                # Route handlers\n│       ├── services/              # Business logic\n│       ├── providers/             # LLM/embedding abstraction + fallback\n│       ├── pipeline/              # Composable write/search pipelines\n│       └── tools/                 # MCP tool implementations\n│\n├── core-storage-api/              # PostgreSQL CRUD microservice\n│   └── src/core_storage_api/\n│       ├── routers/               # Memory, entity, document, fleet CRUD\n│       ├── services/              # ORM operations\n│       └── database/              # SQLAlchemy models, Alembic migrations\n│\n├── plugin/                        # OpenClaw plugin (TypeScript)\n│   └── src/\n│       ├── tools.ts               # Tool implementations\n│       ├── agent-auth.ts          # Per-agent credentials (agent-scoped mc_ keys)\n│       ├── context-engine.ts      # Auto-read/write lifecycle\n│       ├── heartbeat.ts           # 60s heartbeat → MemClaw API\n│       └── educate.ts             # Agent education delivery\n│\n├── common/                        # Shared SQLAlchemy ORM models and constants\n├── tests/                         # Test suite\n├── scripts/                       # Smoke tests, benchmarks, export tools\n├── docker-compose.yml             # Production-like stack\n├── docker-compose.dev.yml         # Dev stack\n└── .env.example                   # Full configuration reference\n```\n\n</details>\n\n<details>\n<summary>Latency benchmarks</summary>\n\nTypical results on a single-instance deployment (OpenAI embeddings + GPT-5.4 Nano):\n\n| Operation | Mean | P50 | P95 |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| `memclaw_write` | ~2000ms | ~2000ms | ~2300ms |\n| `memclaw_recall` | ~650ms | ~640ms | ~670ms |\n| `memclaw_recall` (with `include_brief=true`) | ~1300ms | ~1200ms | ~2100ms |\n\nWrite latency is dominated by LLM enrichment. Recall latency by the embedding API call.\n\n```bash\npython scripts/latency_test.py --url http://localhost:8000 --api-key <admin-key> --runs 20\n```\n\n</details>\n\n---\n\n## Public API & Stability\n\nMemClaw v1.x follows [SemVer 2.0.0](https://semver.org/spec/v2.0.0.html). The surfaces below are stable; everything else is internal and may change in any release.\n\n### Stable surfaces\n\n#### MCP tools (12)\n\nThe MCP server is mounted at `/mcp`. Tool names, parameter names, and the documented op-dispatch values are stable.\n\n| Tool | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `memclaw_recall` | Hybrid semantic + keyword search over memories, with optional LLM-summarised brief. |\n| `memclaw_write` | Single or batch (≤100) memory write; auto-enriched with type, title, summary, tags. |\n| `memclaw_manage` | Per-memory lifecycle, op-dispatched: `read` \\| `update` \\| `transition` \\| `delete` \\| `bulk_delete` \\| `lineage`. |\n| `memclaw_list` | Non-semantic enumeration with filters, sort, cursor pagination. |\n| `memclaw_doc` | Structured-document CRUD, op-dispatched: `write` \\| `read` \\| `query` \\| `delete` \\| `list_collections` \\| `search`. |\n| `memclaw_entity_get` | Look up a knowledge-graph entity by UUID. |\n| `memclaw_tune` | Read/update an agent's per-search profile (top_k, fts_weight, freshness, blend, …). |\n| `memclaw_insights` | Karpathy-Loop reflection: contradictions, failures, stale, divergence, patterns, discover. |\n| `memclaw_evolve` | Karpathy-Loop feedback: record an outcome (`success` \\| `failure` \\| `partial`) against memories. |\n| `memclaw_stats` | Aggregate counts: total + breakdowns by `type` / `agent` / `status`. Read-only. |\n| `memclaw_keystones` | Read mandatory governance rules for the current scope (tenant + fleet + agent merged). Call once per session. |\n| `memclaw_keystones_set` | Author/remove keystone rules, op-dispatched: `set` \\| `delete`. Trust ≥ 1 for self-authored `scope=agent`; ≥ 2 otherwise. |\n\n> Skill sharing uses the generic `memclaw_doc` surface — write/read/query/search/delete on `collection=\"skills\"`. The server validates the slug and embeds `data[\"summary\"]` for semantic discovery (with a back-compat fallback to `data[\"description\"]` for skills).\n\n#### REST endpoints\n\nAll paths are prefixed with `/api/v1` unless noted. Request and response shapes documented in the OpenAPI schema at `/openapi.json` are part of the contract.\n\n| Area | Endpoints |\n|---|---|\n| Memory | `GET/POST /memories`, `PATCH /memories/{id}`, `DELETE /memories/{id}`, `PATCH /memories/{id}/status`, `POST /memories/bulk`, `POST /memories/bulk-delete`, `GET /memories/stats`, `GET /memories/{id}`, `GET /memories/{id}/contradictions`, `POST /search`, `POST /recall`, `POST /ingest/preview`, `POST /ingest/commit` |\n| Knowledge graph | `GET /entities`, `GET /entities/{id}`, `POST /entities/upsert`, `GET /graph`, `POST /relations/upsert` |\n| Documents | `POST /documents`, `GET /documents`, `GET /documents/{id}`, `POST /documents/query`, `DELETE /documents/{id}` |\n| Keystones | `GET /memclaw/keystones`, `POST /memclaw/keystones`, `DELETE /memclaw/keystones/{doc_id}` |\n| Fleet | `POST /fleet/heartbeat`, `GET /fleet/nodes`, `POST /fleet/commands`, `GET /fleet/commands` |\n| Agents | `GET /agents`, `GET /agents/{id}`, `PATCH /agents/{id}/trust`, `POST /admin/agent-keys/provision` (atomic key + row + trust + fleet), `GET /whoami` (identity probe) |\n| Insights | `POST /insights/generate` |\n| Evolve | `POST /evolve/report` |\n| Crystallizer | `POST /crystallize`, `POST /crystallize/all`, `GET /crystallize/reports`, `GET /crystallize/latest` |\n| Settings | `GET/PUT /settings` |\n| System | `GET /health`, `GET /version`, `GET /tool-descriptions`, `GET /audit-log` |\n| MCP | `POST /mcp` (Streamable HTTP transport, mounted at app root) |\n| Bootstrap (plugin) | `GET /plugin-source`, `GET /plugin-source-hash`, `GET/POST /install-plugin`, `GET /install-skill`, `GET /skill/memclaw`. Aliased under `/api` (no `/v1`) for one-line installers. |\n\n#### Plugin environment variables\n\nRead by the OpenClaw plugin. The plugin's published name (`memclaw`) and these variables are the public contract; the plugin's TypeScript module structure is internal.\n\n| Var | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `MEMCLAW_API_URL` | Base URL of the core-api server. |\n| `MEMCLAW_API_KEY` | Tenant or admin API key sent in `X-API-Key`. |\n| `MEMCLAW_TENANT_ID` | Optional pre-resolved tenant id; bypasses lookup. |\n| `MEMCLAW_FLEET_ID` | Default fleet id for writes/heartbeat. |\n| `MEMCLAW_NODE_NAME` | Fleet node identifier reported on heartbeat. |\n| `MEMCLAW_AUTO_WRITE_TURNS` | Auto-write turn summaries (default `true`). |\n\n#### Server environment variables\n\nThese mirror the Configuration table above. See it for defaults.\n\n| Group | Vars |\n|---|---|\n| Database | `POSTGRES_HOST`, `POSTGRES_PORT`, `POSTGRES_USER`, `POSTGRES_PASSWORD`, `POSTGRES_DB`, `POSTGRES_USE_IAM_AUTH`, `POSTGRES_REQUIRE_SSL` |\n| Auth | `ADMIN_API_KEY`, `MEMCLAW_API_KEY`, `IS_STANDALONE` |\n| Providers | `EMBEDDING_PROVIDER`, `ENTITY_EXTRACTION_PROVIDER`, `OPENAI_API_KEY`, `ANTHROPIC_API_KEY`, `OPENROUTER_API_KEY`, `GEMINI_API_KEY`, `USE_LLM_FOR_MEMORY_CREATION` |\n| Runtime | `CORS_ORIGINS`, `ENVIRONMENT`, `SETTINGS_ENCRYPTION_KEY`, `REDIS_URL` |\n\n#### Auth modes\n\n| Mode | Activated by | Use case |\n|---|---|---|\n| Standalone | `IS_STANDALONE=true` | Single-tenant self-host; auth bypassed. |\n| Multi-tenant admin | `ADMIN_API_KEY=…` | Operator key for multi-tenant deployments. |\n| Shared gate | `MEMCLAW_API_KEY=…` | Optional shared secret required on every non-admin request. |","lineStart":760,"lineEnd":889,"totalLines":965,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/README.md","time":{"start":1780728425357,"end":1780728425372}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0336b23a44de4dc5016a23c2693ff88191980bccfb16785a80"}},"id":"prt_e9baf6b8a001hs11b5wPkO7RxZ","sessionID":"ses_164517a7effe3vNYDW5PuSLbjT","messageID":"msg_e9baf44e00018JKlzY23UWrTRW"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780728425375,"sessionID":"ses_164517a7effe3vNYDW5PuSLbjT","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_5DUUCsh0kLIlro44XgwmZ6vR","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-operations/src/core_operations/app.py","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-operations/src/core_operations/app.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"FastAPI application for core-operations.\n2: \n3: Hosts cron/scheduled background jobs that operate on OSS data\n4: (memories, organizations, tenants). No business HTTP surface — only\n5: ``/healthz`` for Cloud Run probes.\n6: \n7: Lifespan ordering:\n8: 1. ``configure_logging`` reads env BEFORE any module that emits log records.\n9: 2. If ``settings.standalone``: skip scheduler entirely. The service runs\n10:    as a no-op; OSS standalone deployments should not deploy this image\n11:    at all, but the flag is a defensive short-circuit.\n12: 3. Otherwise: register cron jobs via ``scheduler.register(...)`` and call\n13:    ``scheduler.start()``. Each registration is its own follow-up ticket\n14:    (CAURA-655 lifecycle migration, CAURA-656 memory retention, etc.) —\n15:    this scaffold registers nothing.\n16: 4. Shutdown cancels all running tasks and awaits their unwind.\n17: \"\"\"\n18: \n19: from __future__ import annotations\n20: \n21: import contextlib\n22: import logging\n23: from collections.abc import AsyncIterator\n24: \n25: from fastapi import FastAPI, HTTPException\n26: \n27: from common.structlog_config import configure_logging\n28: from core_operations.config import settings\n29: from core_operations.scheduler import scheduler, seconds_until_next_utc_hour\n30: from core_operations.tasks import (\n31:     run_archive_expired_tick,\n32:     run_archive_stale_tick,\n33:     run_crystallize_tick,\n34:     run_entity_link_tick,\n35:     run_insights_tick,\n36:     run_purge_soft_deleted_tick,\n37: )\n38: \n39: logger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n40: \n41: \n42: def _register_scheduled_tasks() -> None:\n43:     # Every lifecycle op is wall-clock aligned to a fixed UTC hour via\n44:     # delay_provider: it fires once a day at its configured hour, never at\n45:     # startup, and never drifts from the boot time. The ``24 * 3600`` arg\n46:     # is the nominal daily period (documentation only — the delay_provider\n47:     # drives the actual firing). Each op gets its own registration so an\n48:     # outage on one can't silently mask the others; their audit rows stay\n49:     # independent. Hours are independently configurable so operators can\n50:     # stagger the jobs; they all default to 02:00 UTC.\n51:     def _daily_at(hour_attr: str):\n52:         # Bind the setting lookup lazily so an operator override applied\n53:         # before start() is still picked up, and recompute each cycle.\n54:         return lambda: seconds_until_next_utc_hour(getattr(settings, hour_attr))\n55: \n56:     scheduler.register(\n57:         \"lifecycle-archive-expired\",\n58:         24 * 3600,\n59:         run_archive_expired_tick,\n60:         delay_provider=_daily_at(\"lifecycle_archive_run_at_hour\"),\n61:     )\n62:     scheduler.register(\n63:         \"lifecycle-archive-stale\",\n64:         24 * 3600,\n65:         run_archive_stale_tick,\n66:         delay_provider=_daily_at(\"lifecycle_archive_run_at_hour\"),\n67:     )\n68:     scheduler.register(\n69:         \"lifecycle-purge-soft-deleted\",\n70:         24 * 3600,\n71:         run_purge_soft_deleted_tick,\n72:         delay_provider=_daily_at(\"lifecycle_purge_run_at_hour\"),\n73:     )\n74:     scheduler.register(\n75:         \"lifecycle-crystallize\",\n76:         24 * 3600,\n77:         run_crystallize_tick,\n78:         delay_provider=_daily_at(\"lifecycle_pipeline_run_at_hour\"),\n79:     )\n80:     scheduler.register(\n81:         \"lifecycle-entity-link\",\n82:         24 * 3600,\n83:         run_entity_link_tick,\n84:         delay_provider=_daily_at(\"lifecycle_pipeline_run_at_hour\"),\n85:     )\n86:     scheduler.register(\n87:         \"lifecycle-insights\",\n88:         24 * 3600,\n89:         run_insights_tick,\n90:         delay_provider=_daily_at(\"lifecycle_insights_run_at_hour\"),\n91:     )\n92: \n93: \n94: @contextlib.asynccontextmanager\n95: async def lifespan(app: FastAPI) -> AsyncIterator[None]:\n96:     # Logging is configured here rather than at module import so test\n97:     # runners that import this module (for `app` collection) don't\n98:     # reconfigure structlog before pytest's caplog activates.\n99:     configure_logging(\n100:         settings.environment,\n101:         settings.log_level,\n102:         json_logs=settings.log_format_json,\n103:         log_file=settings.log_file or None,\n104:     )\n105: \n106:     logger.info(\n107:         \"Starting core-operations\",\n108:         extra={\"environment\": settings.environment, \"standalone\": settings.standalone},\n109:     )\n110: \n111:     if settings.standalone:\n112:         # OSS standalone deployments shouldn't deploy this image at all.\n113:         # If we're here it's a misconfiguration — escalate so it shows up\n114:         # in alerts rather than silently consuming a Cloud Run slot.\n115:         logger.warning(\n116:             \"Standalone mode — scheduler disabled. core-operations is a no-op; \"\n117:             \"this image should not be deployed in standalone.\"\n118:         )\n119:         yield\n120:         logger.info(\"Shutting down core-operations (standalone)\")\n121:         return\n122: \n123:     if not settings.core_api_admin_api_key:\n124:         # Surface the misconfig at startup so operators see it\n125:         # immediately, not after the first cron tick fires and 401s\n126:         # against core-api hours later.\n127:         logger.warning(\n128:             \"CORE_API_ADMIN_API_KEY is unset; every fanout POST will be \"\n129:             \"unauthorised. Set the env var before the next cron interval.\",\n130:         )\n131: \n132:     _register_scheduled_tasks()\n133:     await scheduler.start()\n134:     logger.info(\n135:         \"Scheduler started\",\n136:         extra={\"task_count\": scheduler.task_count},\n137:     )\n138: \n139:     yield\n140: \n141:     logger.info(\"Shutting down core-operations\")\n142:     await scheduler.stop()\n143: \n144: \n145: def create_app() -> FastAPI:\n146:     app = FastAPI(\n147:         title=\"MemClaw core-operations\",\n148:         description=(\n149:             \"Host for OSS cron/scheduled jobs (lifecycle, retention, etc.). \"\n150:             \"No business HTTP routes — only /healthz.\"\n151:         ),\n152:         version=\"1.0.0\",\n153:         lifespan=lifespan,\n154:     )\n155: \n156:     @app.get(\"/healthz\")\n157:     async def healthz() -> dict[str, str]:\n158:         return {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n159: \n160:     @app.get(\"/readyz\")\n161:     async def readyz() -> dict[str, str]:\n162:         # Without this gate Cloud Run/k8s would keep an instance with a\n163:         # crashed scheduler in rotation, looking ready while silently\n164:         # doing nothing.\n165:         if not scheduler.is_healthy:\n166:             raise HTTPException(status_code=503, detail=\"scheduler_degraded\")\n167:         return {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n168: \n169:     return app\n170: \n171: \n172: app = create_app()\n\n(End of file - total 172 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"FastAPI application for core-operations.\n\nHosts cron/scheduled background jobs that operate on OSS data\n(memories, organizations, tenants). No business HTTP surface — only\n``/healthz`` for Cloud Run probes.\n\nLifespan ordering:\n1. ``configure_logging`` reads env BEFORE any module that emits log records.\n2. If ``settings.standalone``: skip scheduler entirely. The service runs\n   as a no-op; OSS standalone deployments should not deploy this image\n   at all, but the flag is a defensive short-circuit.\n3. Otherwise: register cron jobs via ``scheduler.register(...)`` and call\n   ``scheduler.start()``. Each registration is its own follow-up ticket\n   (CAURA-655 lifecycle migration, CAURA-656 memory retention, etc.) —\n   this scaffold registers nothing.\n4. Shutdown cancels all running tasks and awaits their unwind.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-operations/src/core_operations/app.py","text":"\"\"\"FastAPI application for core-operations.\n\nHosts cron/scheduled background jobs that operate on OSS data\n(memories, organizations, tenants). No business HTTP surface — only\n``/healthz`` for Cloud Run probes.\n\nLifespan ordering:\n1. ``configure_logging`` reads env BEFORE any module that emits log records.\n2. If ``settings.standalone``: skip scheduler entirely. The service runs\n   as a no-op; OSS standalone deployments should not deploy this image\n   at all, but the flag is a defensive short-circuit.\n3. Otherwise: register cron jobs via ``scheduler.register(...)`` and call\n   ``scheduler.start()``. Each registration is its own follow-up ticket\n   (CAURA-655 lifecycle migration, CAURA-656 memory retention, etc.) —\n   this scaffold registers nothing.\n4. Shutdown cancels all running tasks and awaits their unwind.\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport contextlib\nimport logging\nfrom collections.abc import AsyncIterator\n\nfrom fastapi import FastAPI, HTTPException\n\nfrom common.structlog_config import configure_logging\nfrom core_operations.config import settings\nfrom core_operations.scheduler import scheduler, seconds_until_next_utc_hour\nfrom core_operations.tasks import (\n    run_archive_expired_tick,\n    run_archive_stale_tick,\n    run_crystallize_tick,\n    run_entity_link_tick,\n    run_insights_tick,\n    run_purge_soft_deleted_tick,\n)\n\nlogger = logging.getLogger(__name__)\n\n\ndef _register_scheduled_tasks() -> None:\n    # Every lifecycle op is wall-clock aligned to a fixed UTC hour via\n    # delay_provider: it fires once a day at its configured hour, never at\n    # startup, and never drifts from the boot time. The ``24 * 3600`` arg\n    # is the nominal daily period (documentation only — the delay_provider\n    # drives the actual firing). Each op gets its own registration so an\n    # outage on one can't silently mask the others; their audit rows stay\n    # independent. Hours are independently configurable so operators can\n    # stagger the jobs; they all default to 02:00 UTC.\n    def _daily_at(hour_attr: str):\n        # Bind the setting lookup lazily so an operator override applied\n        # before start() is still picked up, and recompute each cycle.\n        return lambda: seconds_until_next_utc_hour(getattr(settings, hour_attr))\n\n    scheduler.register(\n        \"lifecycle-archive-expired\",\n        24 * 3600,\n        run_archive_expired_tick,\n        delay_provider=_daily_at(\"lifecycle_archive_run_at_hour\"),\n    )\n    scheduler.register(\n        \"lifecycle-archive-stale\",\n        24 * 3600,\n        run_archive_stale_tick,\n        delay_provider=_daily_at(\"lifecycle_archive_run_at_hour\"),\n    )\n    scheduler.register(\n        \"lifecycle-purge-soft-deleted\",\n        24 * 3600,\n        run_purge_soft_deleted_tick,\n        delay_provider=_daily_at(\"lifecycle_purge_run_at_hour\"),\n    )\n    scheduler.register(\n        \"lifecycle-crystallize\",\n        24 * 3600,\n        run_crystallize_tick,\n        delay_provider=_daily_at(\"lifecycle_pipeline_run_at_hour\"),\n    )\n    scheduler.register(\n        \"lifecycle-entity-link\",\n        24 * 3600,\n        run_entity_link_tick,\n        delay_provider=_daily_at(\"lifecycle_pipeline_run_at_hour\"),\n    )\n    scheduler.register(\n        \"lifecycle-insights\",\n        24 * 3600,\n        run_insights_tick,\n        delay_provider=_daily_at(\"lifecycle_insights_run_at_hour\"),\n    )\n\n\n@contextlib.asynccontextmanager\nasync def lifespan(app: FastAPI) -> AsyncIterator[None]:\n    # Logging is configured here rather than at module import so test\n    # runners that import this module (for `app` collection) don't\n    # reconfigure structlog before pytest's caplog activates.\n    configure_logging(\n        settings.environment,\n        settings.log_level,\n        json_logs=settings.log_format_json,\n        log_file=settings.log_file or None,\n    )\n\n    logger.info(\n        \"Starting core-operations\",\n        extra={\"environment\": settings.environment, \"standalone\": settings.standalone},\n    )\n\n    if settings.standalone:\n        # OSS standalone deployments shouldn't deploy this image at all.\n        # If we're here it's a misconfiguration — escalate so it shows up\n        # in alerts rather than silently consuming a Cloud Run slot.\n        logger.warning(\n            \"Standalone mode — scheduler disabled. core-operations is a no-op; \"\n            \"this image should not be deployed in standalone.\"\n        )\n        yield\n        logger.info(\"Shutting down core-operations (standalone)\")\n        return\n\n    if not settings.core_api_admin_api_key:\n        # Surface the misconfig at startup so operators see it\n        # immediately, not after the first cron tick fires and 401s\n        # against core-api hours later.\n        logger.warning(\n            \"CORE_API_ADMIN_API_KEY is unset; every fanout POST will be \"\n            \"unauthorised. Set the env var before the next cron interval.\",\n        )\n\n    _register_scheduled_tasks()\n    await scheduler.start()\n    logger.info(\n        \"Scheduler started\",\n        extra={\"task_count\": scheduler.task_count},\n    )\n\n    yield\n\n    logger.info(\"Shutting down core-operations\")\n    await scheduler.stop()\n\n\ndef create_app() -> FastAPI:\n    app = FastAPI(\n        title=\"MemClaw core-operations\",\n        description=(\n            \"Host for OSS cron/scheduled jobs (lifecycle, retention, etc.). \"\n            \"No business HTTP routes — only /healthz.\"\n        ),\n        version=\"1.0.0\",\n        lifespan=lifespan,\n    )\n\n    @app.get(\"/healthz\")\n    async def healthz() -> dict[str, str]:\n        return {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n\n    @app.get(\"/readyz\")\n    async def readyz() -> dict[str, str]:\n        # Without this gate Cloud Run/k8s would keep an instance with a\n        # crashed scheduler in rotation, looking ready while silently\n        # doing nothing.\n        if not scheduler.is_healthy:\n            raise HTTPException(status_code=503, detail=\"scheduler_degraded\")\n        return {\"status\": \"ok\"}\n\n    return app\n\n\napp = create_app()","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":172,"totalLines":172,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-operations/src/core_operations/app.py","time":{"start":1780728425361,"end":1780728425373}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0336b23a44de4dc5016a23c269400481918dc8d4a417ee01c3"}},"id":"prt_e9baf6b90001tHRbQk1CiN0ial","sessionID":"ses_164517a7effe3vNYDW5PuSLbjT","messageID":"msg_e9baf44e00018JKlzY23UWrTRW"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780728425375,"sessionID":"ses_164517a7effe3vNYDW5PuSLbjT","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_o839pR8yNLXFxVUnQ5ZyRthF","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-operations/src/core_operations/config.py","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-operations/src/core_operations/config.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: \"\"\"Service configuration — env vars validated at startup.\"\"\"\n2: \n3: from __future__ import annotations\n4: \n5: from typing import Literal\n6: \n7: from pydantic import ValidationInfo, field_validator\n8: from pydantic_settings import BaseSettings, SettingsConfigDict\n9: \n10: \n11: class Settings(BaseSettings):\n12:     model_config = SettingsConfigDict(env_file=\".env\", extra=\"ignore\")\n13: \n14:     environment: Literal[\"development\", \"production\", \"sandbox\"] = \"development\"\n15: \n16:     log_level: str = \"INFO\"\n17:     log_format_json: bool = False\n18:     log_file: str = \"\"\n19: \n20:     # When True, the scheduler skips registration and start. OSS standalone\n21:     # deployments should not deploy core-operations at all; this flag is a\n22:     # defensive short-circuit so that an accidentally-started instance\n23:     # exits cleanly rather than firing cron jobs against a single-tenant\n24:     # standalone DB.\n25:     standalone: bool = False\n26: \n27:     # core-storage-api URL for cron tasks that mutate data — the only\n28:     # service permitted to touch the OSS DB directly. Defaults to the\n29:     # local docker-compose service name.\n30:     core_storage_api_url: str = \"http://oss-core-storage-api:8002\"\n31: \n32:     storage_http_timeout_s: float = 30.0\n33: \n34:     # CAURA-655: core-operations doesn't talk to the DB directly — its\n35:     # cron ticks POST to core-api's ``/admin/lifecycle/fanout/<action>``\n36:     # endpoints, which do the org enumeration and Pub/Sub publish.\n37:     core_api_url: str = \"http://oss-core-api:8000\"\n38:     core_api_admin_api_key: str = \"\"\n39: \n40:     # All lifecycle crons are wall-clock aligned to a fixed UTC hour\n41:     # rather than a boot-relative interval: each runs once a day at its\n42:     # configured hour, so it lands in a predictable off-peak window and\n43:     # never drifts with redeploys (and never fires an immediate tick at\n44:     # startup). Each knob is independently tunable so an operator can\n45:     # stagger the jobs across the night; they all default to 02:00 UTC.\n46:     # Per-org scheduling isn't supported here — a single global tick fans\n47:     # out to every active org; enterprise's per-org configurable cadences\n48:     # (e.g. ``security_audit.schedule_cron``) still live on its scheduler.\n49: \n50:     # SQL-only archive ops (expired + stale share this hour).\n51:     lifecycle_archive_run_at_hour: int = 2\n52:     # Purge is operationally a different concern (compliance-driven\n53:     # retention vs. staleness archival), so it gets its own hour and can\n54:     # be moved off the archive slot.\n55:     lifecycle_purge_run_at_hour: int = 2\n56:     # Pipeline ops (crystallize + entity-link) — LLM-heavy, so an operator\n57:     # may want these in their own off-peak slot away from the lighter SQL\n58:     # ops. The consumer-side dedup gate still filters double-fires.\n59:     lifecycle_pipeline_run_at_hour: int = 2\n60:     # Insights discovery (focus='discover'). Opt-in per-org\n61:     # (``auto_insights_enabled``, default off); the consumer's activity\n62:     # gate further no-ops ticks where no non-insight memories landed since\n63:     # the last run, so a once-a-day fire is plenty.\n64:     lifecycle_insights_run_at_hour: int = 2\n65: \n66:     @field_validator(\n67:         \"lifecycle_archive_run_at_hour\",\n68:         \"lifecycle_purge_run_at_hour\",\n69:         \"lifecycle_pipeline_run_at_hour\",\n70:         \"lifecycle_insights_run_at_hour\",\n71:     )\n72:     @classmethod\n73:     def _validate_run_at_hour(cls, v: int, info: ValidationInfo) -> int:\n74:         if not 0 <= v <= 23:\n75:             raise ValueError(f\"{info.field_name} must be in 0..23 (UTC hour)\")\n76:         return v\n77: \n78: \n79: settings = Settings()  # type: ignore[call-arg]\n\n(End of file - total 79 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\"\"\"Service configuration — env vars validated at startup.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom typing import Literal\n\nfrom pydantic import ValidationInfo, field_validator\nfrom pydantic_settings import BaseSettings, SettingsConfigDict\n\n\nclass Settings(BaseSettings):\n    model_config = SettingsConfigDict(env_file=\".env\", extra=\"ignore\")\n\n    environment: Literal[\"development\", \"production\", \"sandbox\"] = \"development\"\n\n    log_level: str = \"INFO\"\n    log_format_json: bool = False\n    log_file: str = \"\"\n\n    # When True, the scheduler skips registration and start. OSS standalone","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-operations/src/core_operations/config.py","text":"\"\"\"Service configuration — env vars validated at startup.\"\"\"\n\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nfrom typing import Literal\n\nfrom pydantic import ValidationInfo, field_validator\nfrom pydantic_settings import BaseSettings, SettingsConfigDict\n\n\nclass Settings(BaseSettings):\n    model_config = SettingsConfigDict(env_file=\".env\", extra=\"ignore\")\n\n    environment: Literal[\"development\", \"production\", \"sandbox\"] = \"development\"\n\n    log_level: str = \"INFO\"\n    log_format_json: bool = False\n    log_file: str = \"\"\n\n    # When True, the scheduler skips registration and start. OSS standalone\n    # deployments should not deploy core-operations at all; this flag is a\n    # defensive short-circuit so that an accidentally-started instance\n    # exits cleanly rather than firing cron jobs against a single-tenant\n    # standalone DB.\n    standalone: bool = False\n\n    # core-storage-api URL for cron tasks that mutate data — the only\n    # service permitted to touch the OSS DB directly. Defaults to the\n    # local docker-compose service name.\n    core_storage_api_url: str = \"http://oss-core-storage-api:8002\"\n\n    storage_http_timeout_s: float = 30.0\n\n    # CAURA-655: core-operations doesn't talk to the DB directly — its\n    # cron ticks POST to core-api's ``/admin/lifecycle/fanout/<action>``\n    # endpoints, which do the org enumeration and Pub/Sub publish.\n    core_api_url: str = \"http://oss-core-api:8000\"\n    core_api_admin_api_key: str = \"\"\n\n    # All lifecycle crons are wall-clock aligned to a fixed UTC hour\n    # rather than a boot-relative interval: each runs once a day at its\n    # configured hour, so it lands in a predictable off-peak window and\n    # never drifts with redeploys (and never fires an immediate tick at\n    # startup). Each knob is independently tunable so an operator can\n    # stagger the jobs across the night; they all default to 02:00 UTC.\n    # Per-org scheduling isn't supported here — a single global tick fans\n    # out to every active org; enterprise's per-org configurable cadences\n    # (e.g. ``security_audit.schedule_cron``) still live on its scheduler.\n\n    # SQL-only archive ops (expired + stale share this hour).\n    lifecycle_archive_run_at_hour: int = 2\n    # Purge is operationally a different concern (compliance-driven\n    # retention vs. staleness archival), so it gets its own hour and can\n    # be moved off the archive slot.\n    lifecycle_purge_run_at_hour: int = 2\n    # Pipeline ops (crystallize + entity-link) — LLM-heavy, so an operator\n    # may want these in their own off-peak slot away from the lighter SQL\n    # ops. The consumer-side dedup gate still filters double-fires.\n    lifecycle_pipeline_run_at_hour: int = 2\n    # Insights discovery (focus='discover'). Opt-in per-org\n    # (``auto_insights_enabled``, default off); the consumer's activity\n    # gate further no-ops ticks where no non-insight memories landed since\n    # the last run, so a once-a-day fire is plenty.\n    lifecycle_insights_run_at_hour: int = 2\n\n    @field_validator(\n        \"lifecycle_archive_run_at_hour\",\n        \"lifecycle_purge_run_at_hour\",\n        \"lifecycle_pipeline_run_at_hour\",\n        \"lifecycle_insights_run_at_hour\",\n    )\n    @classmethod\n    def _validate_run_at_hour(cls, v: int, info: ValidationInfo) -> int:\n        if not 0 <= v <= 23:\n            raise ValueError(f\"{info.field_name} must be in 0..23 (UTC hour)\")\n        return v\n\n\nsettings = Settings()  # type: ignore[call-arg]","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":79,"totalLines":79,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/core-operations/src/core_operations/config.py","time":{"start":1780728425363,"end":1780728425374}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0336b23a44de4dc5016a23c269400c8191b1dd8bde2b6c1b98"}},"id":"prt_e9baf6b92001ntTK01kTmiAGWq","sessionID":"ses_164517a7effe3vNYDW5PuSLbjT","messageID":"msg_e9baf44e00018JKlzY23UWrTRW"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1780728425665,"sessionID":"ses_164517a7effe3vNYDW5PuSLbjT","part":{"id":"prt_e9baf6cbf001GRZg8UVqMWJjjk","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"cde5d27ecc6fbe7a9c27e741a21d0daa81a7d52c","messageID":"msg_e9baf44e00018JKlzY23UWrTRW","sessionID":"ses_164517a7effe3vNYDW5PuSLbjT","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":68716,"input":15051,"output":400,"reasoning":17,"cache":{"write":0,"read":53248}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1780728427631,"sessionID":"ses_164517a7effe3vNYDW5PuSLbjT","part":{"id":"prt_e9baf746d001IjXseUYQgL2cY1","messageID":"msg_e9baf6df7001M6Z39Pp2ndjNxn","sessionID":"ses_164517a7effe3vNYDW5PuSLbjT","snapshot":"61dc15e6e7c80a049d6af1d866ae880ac960875f","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1780728430338,"sessionID":"ses_164517a7effe3vNYDW5PuSLbjT","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_NTjGrXE4xCuIRgo7K486enAQ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/README.md","offset":270,"limit":40},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n270: \n271: ### Integrations\n272: \n273: - **MCP server** — built-in [Model Context Protocol](https://modelcontextprotocol.io) at `/mcp` (Streamable HTTP). Connect Claude Desktop, Claude Code, Cursor, Windsurf, or any MCP client with a URL and API key\n274: - **Multi-provider LLM** — primary + fallback provider chain per tenant (OpenAI, Gemini, Anthropic, OpenRouter) with platform defaults for zero-config tenants\n275: - **Document store** — structured JSONB collections alongside semantic memories for exact-field lookups (customer records, config, task lists)\n276: \n277: ---\n278: \n279: ## Performance\n280: \n281: Benchmarked against the two most-cited public agent-memory benchmarks. Methodology and operator-scale context live in [`docs/performance.md`](docs/performance.md); the full write-up is on the blog.\n282: \n283: |  | LoCoMo | LongMemEval | Search latency |\n284: |---|---|---|---|\n285: | Accuracy (LLM-judge) | **77.6%** | **72.5%** | — |\n286: | Token savings vs full context | **96.6%** | **98.2%** | — |\n287: | Latency | — | — | **23 ms p50 · 27 ms p95** |\n288: \n289: Accuracy sits inside the leading cluster across the field (Mem0, Zep, MemClaw — scores cluster in a narrow band). The axes we push hardest are latency and token efficiency, because those are the ones that compound as agent count grows — a few hundred ms of search latency disappears behind one LLM call, but bills millions of times a day across a fleet.\n290: \n291: > Single-agent benchmarks can't measure cross-agent recall, outcome propagation between agents, fleet-scoped visibility, or governance-aware retrieval. Those are the questions that decide whether a memory system is *deployable* inside a company. See [`docs/performance.md`](docs/performance.md#what-these-benchmarks-cant-measure).\n292: \n293: Source: [Fast, Token-Efficient, and Built for Fleets](https://memclaw.net/blog/memclaw-benchmarks) (2026-04-19).\n294: \n295: ---\n296: \n297: ## MCP (Model Context Protocol)\n298: \n299: Add MemClaw to any MCP client with one config block.\n300: \n301: **Self-hosted** (localhost):\n302: \n303: ```json\n304: {\n305:   \"mcpServers\": {\n306:     \"memclaw\": {\n307:       \"url\": \"http://localhost:8000/mcp\",\n308:       \"headers\": { \"X-API-Key\": \"standalone\" }\n309:     }\n\n(Showing lines 270-309 of 965. Use offset=310 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n### Integrations\n\n- **MCP server** — built-in [Model Context Protocol](https://modelcontextprotocol.io) at `/mcp` (Streamable HTTP). Connect Claude Desktop, Claude Code, Cursor, Windsurf, or any MCP client with a URL and API key\n- **Multi-provider LLM** — primary + fallback provider chain per tenant (OpenAI, Gemini, Anthropic, OpenRouter) with platform defaults for zero-config tenants\n- **Document store** — structured JSONB collections alongside semantic memories for exact-field lookups (customer records, config, task lists)\n\n---\n\n## Performance\n\nBenchmarked against the two most-cited public agent-memory benchmarks. Methodology and operator-scale context live in [`docs/performance.md`](docs/performance.md); the full write-up is on the blog.\n\n|  | LoCoMo | LongMemEval | Search latency |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Accuracy (LLM-judge) | **77.6%** | **72.5%** | — |\n| Token savings vs full context | **96.6%** | **98.2%** | — |\n| Latency | — | — | **23 ms p50 · 27 ms p95** |\n\nAccuracy sits inside the leading cluster across the field (Mem0, Zep, MemClaw — scores cluster in a narrow band). The axes we push hardest are latency and token efficiency, because those are the ones that compound as agent count grows — a few hundred ms of search latency disappears behind one LLM call, but bills millions of times a day across a fleet.","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/README.md","text":"\n### Integrations\n\n- **MCP server** — built-in [Model Context Protocol](https://modelcontextprotocol.io) at `/mcp` (Streamable HTTP). Connect Claude Desktop, Claude Code, Cursor, Windsurf, or any MCP client with a URL and API key\n- **Multi-provider LLM** — primary + fallback provider chain per tenant (OpenAI, Gemini, Anthropic, OpenRouter) with platform defaults for zero-config tenants\n- **Document store** — structured JSONB collections alongside semantic memories for exact-field lookups (customer records, config, task lists)\n\n---\n\n## Performance\n\nBenchmarked against the two most-cited public agent-memory benchmarks. Methodology and operator-scale context live in [`docs/performance.md`](docs/performance.md); the full write-up is on the blog.\n\n|  | LoCoMo | LongMemEval | Search latency |\n|---|---|---|---|\n| Accuracy (LLM-judge) | **77.6%** | **72.5%** | — |\n| Token savings vs full context | **96.6%** | **98.2%** | — |\n| Latency | — | — | **23 ms p50 · 27 ms p95** |\n\nAccuracy sits inside the leading cluster across the field (Mem0, Zep, MemClaw — scores cluster in a narrow band). The axes we push hardest are latency and token efficiency, because those are the ones that compound as agent count grows — a few hundred ms of search latency disappears behind one LLM call, but bills millions of times a day across a fleet.\n\n> Single-agent benchmarks can't measure cross-agent recall, outcome propagation between agents, fleet-scoped visibility, or governance-aware retrieval. Those are the questions that decide whether a memory system is *deployable* inside a company. See [`docs/performance.md`](docs/performance.md#what-these-benchmarks-cant-measure).\n\nSource: [Fast, Token-Efficient, and Built for Fleets](https://memclaw.net/blog/memclaw-benchmarks) (2026-04-19).\n\n---\n\n## MCP (Model Context Protocol)\n\nAdd MemClaw to any MCP client with one config block.\n\n**Self-hosted** (localhost):\n\n```json\n{\n  \"mcpServers\": {\n    \"memclaw\": {\n      \"url\": \"http://localhost:8000/mcp\",\n      \"headers\": { \"X-API-Key\": \"standalone\" }\n    }","lineStart":270,"lineEnd":309,"totalLines":965,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/027-xce-research-based-refinement/external/caura-memclaw-main/README.md","time":{"start":1780728430334,"end":1780728430338}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0111c5499fdd7160016a23c26e0a688191ab636d5c017469d7"}},"id":"prt_e9baf7dfe001zd3srGOiBWb1n4","sessionID":"ses_164517a7effe3vNYDW5PuSLbjT","messageID":"msg_e9baf6df7001M6Z39Pp2ndjNxn"}}
